    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1891-02-14T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1891-02-14T00:00:00-05:00" n="350" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d350">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Blaine</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Denby</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-02-14">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 14,
                            1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 590.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 1212, of December 13
                        last, and a copy of the latest note of the yamén in the McCaslin case, which
                        you inclose, declining to open up the judgment at Ningpo.</p>
                <p>Your suggestion that the case will have to be reserved for the present is
                        approved. It might be well for you, however, to reply to the yamén’s note,
                        in order that we may not seem to have acquiesced in it, and that the issue
                        may be kept distinct and our rights reserved.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">James G. Blaine</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
